<TITLE> Stocks decline in morning trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 10 (bdnews24.com) The market opened downbeat Monday, with the general index falling at start of trade. It recovered some points in the second hour of trading, but declined again round midday and continued to fall. At 12.07 pm, the DGEN or general index was down 10.8) points or ).36 percent at 2918.07. The DSI or all share price index fell 9.09 points or 0.36 percent at 2466.06 Of the issues traded 52 advanced, 112 declined and 13 remained unchanged. At 12.14 pm, UCBL emerged at the top of share value board. It was selling at Tk 4955 from Sunday's Tk 4942.5. ACI was selling high at Tk 185.8 from the previous day's closing of Tk 179.3. Islami Bank Perpetual Bond, a recent entrant in the market, declined to Tk 1497 from Sunday's closing price of Tk 1515.25. Market heavyweight Summit Power was selling down at Tk 1494.75 from Tk 1511. BOC Bangladesh declined after gaining the previous day on rumors of a possible merger or takeover. It was selling at Tk 324.5 from Tk 328.7. Other scrips on the top-ten share value boardBRAC Bank, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh, Prime Bank and BATBCalso fell, while Berger Paints Bangladesh Ltd increased. bdn
